@sxjscience Tried. The PR fixed the problem. Thank you!
Env: Windows server 2012, K40m, CUDA 7.0, cudnn v4
mxnet version: eaa5bda94e313b9b6a55a8d8632aff96f0e153ab

from example and the code implementation in kvstore_dist_server.h,
I find when use kvstore_server, the updater mush be set by call set_optimizer in the worker node, before call kvstore push.
when just use local version kvstore, the updater can be default as the "Assign" operation, which is consistent with the doc.
I have a question why there can't be default assignment behavior in kvstore server?
for example, the code in 

```
void DataHandle(const ps::KVMeta& req_meta,
                  const ps::KVPairs<real_t>& req_data,
                  ps::KVServer<real_t>* server) {
```

can such code

```
 // async push
        exec_.Exec([this, key, &recved, &stored](){
          CHECK(updater_);
          updater_(key, recved, &stored);
        });
        server->Response(req_meta);
        stored.WaitToRead();
```

be modified to

```
 // async push
        if(updater_ != nullptr){
          exec_.Exec([this, key, &recved, &stored](){
            CHECK(updater_);
            updater_(key, recved, &stored);
          });
        } else {
          CopyFromTo(recved, &stored, 0);
        }
        server->Response(req_meta);
        stored.WaitToRead();
```

?
and sorry, another question, after try them all, I guess kvstore is not design as I read from its name, a key-value storage and support distribution.
directly use it to share value in different process is not easy (finaly, i only achieved in the 'dist-async' mode, the 'dist-sync' mode will blocking when call push).
maybe It try to do some automatic work for parameter-server.
and, If I want use serveral workers for training and one worker just pull param only for prediction. is there any convenient way by using kvstore? or I should do the communication by myself like use multiprocessing?

Thank you for your kind advice. Tried but as soon i solve an error, another one appear. I guess this is not as simple as with Python yet :/

